Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.89,0:00:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)}On the first floor of a wood apartment, \Nhe drew, completely engrossed in painting
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.64,0:00:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,150)}What he'd wanted to paint was his own self,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.45,0:00:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(150,0)}a world that would surround and capture him
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.97,0:00:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,150)}Ever since he was little, he liked drawing
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.96,0:00:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(150,200)}That was because everyone praised him for it
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.26,0:00:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)}But now, the only one who praises him
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.64,0:00:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,450)}is his girlfriend living with him
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.98,0:01:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,150)}But that was all he needed to be happy
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.94,0:01:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(150,150)}Each day, they happened to miss each other
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.89,0:01:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(150,150)}but she always left him letters
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.33,0:01:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(150,150)}on sakura-patterned stationery; those were dear to him
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.60,0:01:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)}Before they knew it, the night had ended
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.64,0:01:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)}Before they knew it, the sun had set
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.64,0:01:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)}Before they knew it, winter had reached its end
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.22,0:01:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)}That day, for the first time, his art sold
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.97,0:01:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)}By then, their circumstances had begun to constantly change
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.52,0:01:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)}The next month, all his paintings sold
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.68,0:01:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,500)}And what kept on changing was always the scenery...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.80,0:01:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)}Everyone praised his paintings
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.55,0:02:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)}And she happily told him this:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.59,0:02:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,500)}"I was right to have believed..."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.57,0:02:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,500)}"I was right to have..."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.60,0:02:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)}Sometimes, he received thank-you letters\Nfrom the people who bought his art
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.47,0:02:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)}He had no memory of ever being thanked,\Nbut it didn't feel strange, either
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.64,0:02:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)}The small room began to fill bit by bit\Nwith treasures, which made him happy
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.06,0:02:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,500)}And he thought to himself how wonderful\Nit'd be if things could stay like this forever...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.85,0:02:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)}He began to like drawing even more and more
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.73,0:02:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)}He wanted to create even grander paintings
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.72,0:02:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)}What he wanted to paint was his own self,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.72,0:02:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,500)}to paint an even closer truth
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.56,0:03:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)}He finished his greatest masterpiece
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.81,0:03:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)}Even she smiled and said, "It's wonderful"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.02,0:03:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,1500)}It was a painting of the true miserable nature of humans,\None that would make anyone turn their eyes away...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.31,0:03:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)}Everyone knitted their eyebrows in disgust at his painting
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.93,0:03:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,500)}Retreating like the water's tide, each and every one person left
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.22,0:03:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,500)}And what kept on changing was always the scenery...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.52,0:03:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)}The people all ridiculed him, calling him incompetent
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.98,0:03:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)}Their fights increasing, the two of them eventually broke up
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.89,0:03:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)}Was I wrong to have believed...?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.68,0:04:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,0)}Was I wrong to have...?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.96,0:04:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)}On the first floor of a wood apartment,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.77,0:04:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)}he continues to draw, even now
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.63,0:04:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)}What I'd wanted to paint was my own self,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.46,0:04:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)}what turned out to be an empty shell of my own self...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.29,0:04:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)}I've liked drawing ever since I was little
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.06,0:04:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)}Now, I don't even know why anymore
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.45,0:04:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)}There's no one left who'll praise me
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.37,0:04:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)}There's no more names I can give\Nto these piles of paintings sitting here
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.64,0:05:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)}How many months, how many years have passed without me realizing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.45,0:05:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)}That day, for the first time in a while, a single painting of mine sold
